            <p class="mt-2 text-[0.88rem] leading-[1.6] text-muted-text">Real cone breakup depends on thickness (∝ t), curvature (curvilinear profiles raise fb by 20–40%), edge compliance (real surrounds lower fb by 15–25%), and anisotropy (woven materials differ 2× between warp and weft). The tool collapses all of this into a single material multiplier. Two 15 cm aluminum cones from different manufacturers can have fb anywhere from 5 kHz to 9 kHz. Use the override slider if you have a measured fb — the material selector is for qualitative exploration.</p>
